President Biden hosted Prime Minister Narendra Modi to strengthen the relationship between the United States and India. The two countries, as the world's oldest and largest democracies, share a commitment to freedom, pluralism, openness, and human rights. The leaders discussed various areas of cooperation, including working together on the world stage, protecting the planet and promoting clean energy, generating jobs and mutual prosperity, advancing security in the Indo-Pacific region, exploring space, and reinvigorating science, education, innovation, and people-to-people ties.